    <div class="container">
        <h1>Red Fort</h1>
        <img src="redfort.png" alt="Red Fort" />
        <p>
            The Red Fort is a historic fort in the city of Delhi in India. It was built by the Mughal
            Emperor Shah Jahan in the 17th century. The fort served as the main residence of the
            emperors of the Mughal dynasty for nearly 200 years until 1857.
        </p>
        <p>
            The Red Fort is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and is an iconic symbol of India's rich history
            and cultural heritage. The fort's impressive architecture and red sandstone walls are a
            testament to the grandeur of the Mughal era.
        </p>
        <p>
            The complex of the Red Fort includes various structures like Diwan-i-Aam (Hall of Public
            Audience), Diwan-i-Khas (Hall of Private Audience), Rang Mahal (Palace of Colors), and the
            beautiful gardens that add to its charm.
        </p>
    </div>
